verbose_text: The present study has demonstrated that CYP2C8 derived EETs significantly suppressed TNF-alpha-induced intracellular ROS formation and the redox sensitive NF-kappaB activation via the suppression of IkappaB degradation and phosphorylation.
evidence: CYP2C8-derived EETs significantly suppressed TNF-alpha-induced intracellular ROS formation and the redox-sensitive NF-kappaB activation via the suppression of IkappaB degradation and phosphorylation
